34static void
35gk20a_gr_init_dtor(struct gf100_gr_pack *pack)
36{
37 vfree(pack);
38}
39
40struct gk20a_fw_av
41{
42 u32 addr;
43 u32 data;
44};
45
46static struct gf100_gr_pack *
47gk20a_gr_av_to_init(struct gf100_gr_fuc *fuc)
48{
49 struct gf100_gr_init *init;
50 struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
51 const int nent = (fuc->size / sizeof(struct gk20a_fw_av));
52 int i;
53
54 pack = vzalloc((sizeof(*pack) * 2) + (sizeof(*init) * (nent + 1)));
55 if (!pack)
56 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
57
58 init = (void *)(pack + 2);
59
60 pack[0].init = init;
61
62 for (i = 0; i < nent; i++) {
63 struct gf100_gr_init *ent = &init[i];
64 struct gk20a_fw_av *av = &((struct gk20a_fw_av *)fuc->data)[i];
65
66 ent->addr = av->addr;
67 ent->data = av->data;
68 ent->count = 1;
69 ent->pitch = 1;
70 }
71
72 return pack;
73}
74
75struct gk20a_fw_aiv
76{
77 u32 addr;
78 u32 index;
79 u32 data;
80};
81
82static struct gf100_gr_pack *
83gk20a_gr_aiv_to_init(struct gf100_gr_fuc *fuc)
84{
85 struct gf100_gr_init *init;
86 struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
87 const int nent = (fuc->size / sizeof(struct gk20a_fw_aiv));
88 int i;
89
90 pack = vzalloc((sizeof(*pack) * 2) + (sizeof(*init) * (nent + 1)));
91 if (!pack)
92 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
93
94 init = (void *)(pack + 2);
95
96 pack[0].init = init;
97
98 for (i = 0; i < nent; i++) {
99 struct gf100_gr_init *ent = &init[i];
100 struct gk20a_fw_aiv *av = &((struct gk20a_fw_aiv *)fuc->data)[i];
101
102 ent->addr = av->addr;
103 ent->data = av->data;
104 ent->count = 1;
105 ent->pitch = 1;
106 }
107
108 return pack;
109}
110
111static struct gf100_gr_pack *
112gk20a_gr_av_to_method(struct gf100_gr_fuc *fuc)
113{
114 struct gf100_gr_init *init;
115 struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
116 /* We don't suppose we will initialize more than 16 classes here... */
117 static const unsigned int max_classes = 16;
118 const int nent = (fuc->size / sizeof(struct gk20a_fw_av));
119 int i, classidx = 0;
120 u32 prevclass = 0;
121
122 pack = vzalloc((sizeof(*pack) * max_classes) +
123 (sizeof(*init) * (nent + 1)));
124 if (!pack)
125 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
126
127 init = (void *)(pack + max_classes);
128
129 for (i = 0; i < nent; i++) {
130 struct gf100_gr_init *ent = &init[i];
131 struct gk20a_fw_av *av = &((struct gk20a_fw_av *)fuc->data)[i];
132 u32 class = av->addr & 0xffff;
133 u32 addr = (av->addr & 0xffff0000) >> 14;
134
135 if (prevclass != class) {
136 pack[classidx].init = ent;
137 pack[classidx].type = class;
138 prevclass = class;
139 if (++classidx >= max_classes) {
140 vfree(pack);
141 return ERR_PTR(-ENOSPC);
142 }
143 }
144
145 ent->addr = addr;
146 ent->data = av->data;
147 ent->count = 1;
148 ent->pitch = 1;
149 }
150
151 return pack;
152}
153
154static int
155gk20a_gr_wait_mem_scrubbing(struct gf100_gr *gr)
156{
157 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
158 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
159
160 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
161 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40910c) & 0x00000006))
162 break;
163 ) < 0) {
164 nvkm_error(subdev, "FECS mem scrubbing timeout\n");
165 return -ETIMEDOUT;
166 }
167
168 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
169 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x41a10c) & 0x00000006))
170 break;
171 ) < 0) {
172 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPCCS mem scrubbing timeout\n");
173 return -ETIMEDOUT;
174 }
175
176 return 0;
177}
178
179static void
180gk20a_gr_set_hww_esr_report_mask(struct gf100_gr *gr)
181{
182 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
183 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419e44, 0x1ffffe);
184 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419e4c, 0x7f);
185}
186
187int
188gk20a_gr_init(struct gf100_gr *gr)
189{
190 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
191 const u32 magicgpc918 = DIV_ROUND_UP(0x00800000, gr->tpc_total);
192 u32 data[TPC_MAX / 8] = {};
193 u8 tpcnr[GPC_MAX];
194 int gpc, tpc;
195 int ret, i;
196
197 /* Clear SCC RAM */
198 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40802c, 0x1);
199
200 gf100_gr_mmio(gr, gr->fuc_sw_nonctx);
201
202 ret = gk20a_gr_wait_mem_scrubbing(gr);
203 if (ret)
204 return ret;
205
206 ret = gf100_gr_wait_idle(gr);
207 if (ret)
208 return ret;
209
210 /* MMU debug buffer */
211 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100cc8, nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b4) >> 8);
212 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100ccc, nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b8) >> 8);
213
214 if (gr->func->init_gpc_mmu)
215 gr->func->init_gpc_mmu(gr);
216
217 /* Set the PE as stream master */
218 nvkm_mask(device, 0x503018, 0x1, 0x1);
219
220 /* Zcull init */
221 memset(data, 0x00, sizeof(data));
222 memcpy(tpcnr, gr->tpc_nr, sizeof(gr->tpc_nr));
223 for (i = 0, gpc = -1; i < gr->tpc_total; i++) {
224 do {
225 gpc = (gpc + 1) % gr->gpc_nr;
226 } while (!tpcnr[gpc]);
227 tpc = gr->tpc_nr[gpc] - tpcnr[gpc]--;
228
229 data[i / 8] |= tpc << ((i % 8) * 4);
230 }
231
232 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0980), data[0]);
233 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0984), data[1]);
234 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0988), data[2]);
235 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x098c), data[3]);
236
237 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
238 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0914),
239 gr->magic_not_rop_nr << 8 | gr->tpc_nr[gpc]);
240 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0910), 0x00040000 |
241 gr->tpc_total);
242 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0918), magicgpc918);
243 }
244
245 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x3fd4), magicgpc918);
246
247 /* Enable FIFO access */
248 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
249
250 /* Enable interrupts */
251 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0xffffffff);
252 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40013c, 0xffffffff);
253
254 /* Enable FECS error interrupts */
255 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c24, 0x000f0000);
256
257 /* Enable hardware warning exceptions */
258 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404000, 0xc0000000);
259 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404600, 0xc0000000);
260
261 if (gr->func->set_hww_esr_report_mask)
262 gr->func->set_hww_esr_report_mask(gr);
263
264 /* Enable TPC exceptions per GPC */
265 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419d0c, 0x2);
266 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41ac94, (((1 << gr->tpc_total) - 1) & 0xff) << 16);
267
268 /* Reset and enable all exceptions */
269 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0xffffffff);
270 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400138, 0xffffffff);
271 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400118, 0xffffffff);
272 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400130, 0xffffffff);
273 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40011c, 0xffffffff);
274 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400134, 0xffffffff);
275
276 gf100_gr_zbc_init(gr);
277
278 return gf100_gr_init_ctxctl(gr);
279}
280
281void
282gk20a_gr_dtor(struct gf100_gr *gr)
283{
284 gk20a_gr_init_dtor(gr->fuc_method);
285 gk20a_gr_init_dtor(gr->fuc_bundle);
286 gk20a_gr_init_dtor(gr->fuc_sw_ctx);
287 gk20a_gr_init_dtor(gr->fuc_sw_nonctx);
288}
289
290int
291gk20a_gr_new_(const struct gf100_gr_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
292 int index, struct nvkm_gr **pgr)
293{
294 struct gf100_gr_fuc fuc;
295 struct gf100_gr *gr;
296 int ret;
297
298 if (!(gr = kzalloc(sizeof(*gr), GFP_KERNEL)))
299 return -ENOMEM;
300 *pgr = &gr->base;
301
302 ret = gf100_gr_ctor(func, device, index, gr);
303 if (ret)
304 return ret;
305
306 ret = gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "sw_nonctx", &fuc);
307 if (ret)
308 return ret;
309 gr->fuc_sw_nonctx = gk20a_gr_av_to_init(&fuc);
310 gf100_gr_dtor_fw(&fuc);
311 if (IS_ERR(gr->fuc_sw_nonctx))
312 return PTR_ERR(gr->fuc_sw_nonctx);
313
314 ret = gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "sw_ctx", &fuc);
315 if (ret)
316 return ret;
317 gr->fuc_sw_ctx = gk20a_gr_aiv_to_init(&fuc);
318 gf100_gr_dtor_fw(&fuc);
319 if (IS_ERR(gr->fuc_sw_ctx))
320 return PTR_ERR(gr->fuc_sw_ctx);
321
322 ret = gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "sw_bundle_init", &fuc);
323 if (ret)
324 return ret;
325 gr->fuc_bundle = gk20a_gr_av_to_init(&fuc);
326 gf100_gr_dtor_fw(&fuc);
327 if (IS_ERR(gr->fuc_bundle))
328 return PTR_ERR(gr->fuc_bundle);
329
330 ret = gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "sw_method_init", &fuc);
331 if (ret)
332 return ret;
333 gr->fuc_method = gk20a_gr_av_to_method(&fuc);
334 gf100_gr_dtor_fw(&fuc);
335 if (IS_ERR(gr->fuc_method))
336 return PTR_ERR(gr->fuc_method);
337
338 return 0;
339}
340
341static const struct gf100_gr_func
342gk20a_gr = {
343 .dtor = gk20a_gr_dtor,
344 .init = gk20a_gr_init,
345 .set_hww_esr_report_mask = gk20a_gr_set_hww_esr_report_mask,
346 .ppc_nr = 1,
347 .grctx = &gk20a_grctx,
348 .sclass = {
349 { -1, -1, FERMI_TWOD_A },
350 { -1, -1, KEPLER_INLINE_TO_MEMORY_A },
351 { -1, -1, KEPLER_C, &gf100_fermi },
352 { -1, -1, KEPLER_COMPUTE_A },
353 {}
354 }
355};
356
357int
358gk20a_gr_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_gr **pgr)
359{
360 return gk20a_gr_new_(&gk20a_gr, device, index, pgr);
361}
